Dear 
Jeffrey,



We had a 
meeting yesterday with 
Juan 
Carlos Molyneux, the notary 

Mr. Chardon, and my partner 

Mr. 
Alain Maillot and myself. I also have had several conversations with the 
members of the family and with their counsel, 
Mr. de Pingon. First of all, we think 
that the deal which has been negotiated by 
Juan 
Carlos Molyneux is excellent. The price 
appears to be fantastic, taking into account the quality of the property and the 
castle.



We suggest 
to speed up the process of the acquisition in order to 
render more difficult the preemption of Guermantes city or any 
other state bodies. We are going to send you a note summarizing our 
suggestions on the structure of acquisition which appears to us the most 
appropriate. In that respect, could you confirm to me that you are a 


US resident for tax 
treaties? The answer to that question is important to set up the best 
acquisition scheme.



All my best,



Matthieu de 
